    "We believe that the integration of digital neural networks with these reconfigurable (ideally jointly-trained) metasurfaces can contribute to a broad range of futuristic information technologies.",
    "Various practical applications of free-space optical systems, such as imaging and computing, require tackling various challenges in device fabrication and performance.",
    "Diffraction efficiency, in particular, is critical for enabling energy-efficient technologies ranging from QPI and microscopy to holographic displays.",
    "Emerging innovations in the design methods and optical materials that can improve output diffraction efficiencies will be discussed in Section \"Diffraction efficiency and power requirements\".",
    "The ability to tune and reconfigure freespace devices during their operation is also critical for various applications, including telecommunications (e.g., active beamforming) and imaging."
